title: Foot path occupation on DeSouza Road, Off Hayes Road, Ward 111, Shanthala Nagar by illegal food cart vendor needs to be stopped
description:
SUB: Foot path occupation on DeSouza Road, Off Hayes Road, Ward 111, Shanthala Nagar by illegal food cart vendor needs to be stopped

Sir,

This is to bring to your attention the CONTINUED inaction of the authorities to curb illegal and dangerous activities in Bangalore in spite of several requests from residents.

 In BBMP Ward 111, Shantala Nagar coming under purview of MLA N A Haris an illegal food cart vendor has set up shop with the backing of local hoteliers on the pavement at the corner of DeSouza Road and Hayes Road (which connects Residency Road and Richmond Road). Desouza Road is a narrow residential street
 Such activity is illegal and needs to be stopped. The illegal stall has also attracted criminal elements peddling drugs and liquor and sex to customers.
 He is obstructing the right of way of pedestrians and polluting the air, road and storm water drains.
 He is using open fire and gas cylinders in the open in close proximity to electric junction boxes, street lights and transformers and fuel tanks of parked vehicles.
 The said vendor also dumps used inflammable oil, waste and other refuse on the road, pavements and storm water drains.
 The surrounding area has turned into an eyesore
 There is now also a rise in number of mosquitoes, flies, rats, dogs due to this

The vendors blocking the pavement on Desouza Road and Hayes Road need to be removed. The footpath is not an area for vendors but it is to be provided for pedestrians.

Desouza Road has as a result become an eyesore in the centre of Bangalore.
Photographic evidence is attached to this email.

Kindly do inspect the area for yourself and get the concerned authorities to act immediately.

Regards,
Sunil
location: 15, Hayes Rd, Shanthala Nagar, Ashok Nagar, Bengaluru, Karnataka 560025, India
address: Close to Vista Spaces Multi-Storey Building Construction Site

title: Misbehaving by fellow BMTC Passengers
description:
It is often seen in BMTC customers keeping theri belongings on seat when bus arrives and then claiming to sit on the seat irrespective of coming late to the bus. Also, there is no action by conductors or drivers against such behaviour.

BMTC being public transport seats are available to customers on first come first serve basis except for physically challenged or senior citizens.

In a same incident today, a lady kept bag on seat when i was just about to sit (Please not i was not even far from the seat) and then started arguing with me to vacate the seat since she kept her bag their and has been travelling on that route since 25 years and the bus belongs to her father(Yes she said this). It was not only argument but she also physically started fighting with me. 

And the conductor and driver instead of asking her to get down or imposing fine on her asked me only to move. I have no problem in shifting to different seat and I understand it was not driver or conductor who started the fight, but this is general rule that there are no reservations in BMTC unlike KSRTC and conductor and driver being representative of BMTC services are responsible to maintain order.

Many times it is noticed that conductor and driver dont come forward to see who is actually wrong even in cases when a senior citizen is standing and while a young person is sitting in seats reserved for them.

The bus was for route "Singapura - Vidhana Soudha" 271c at 8:30 am on 24.1.19. Attached are images of scratch marks given by the lady to me also she even slapped me and pulled my hair and even then conductor did not take action against her.
location: Singapura, Bengaluru, Karnataka, India

title: Long parking with no movement & circulation
description: Cars are parked for a very long duration with no one owning up to it. It is parked for months even years with no movement. At Castle street, Tate Lane, Wood street, which is the city business district  wherein people park the car and leave the car for months even years. Moreover people who park do not even live closeby, they live elsewhere and park at prime locations making it immensely difficult or even impossible for people who live and work on that road to find parking hence parking on the roadside thereby adding to the traffic woes and reducing the vehicle carriageway. If there is a rotation of parking, there will be movement.We would like to indicate that our road has cars parked for a very long duration and collected a thick layer of dust,leaves,etc . To avoid the dust now they have also covered their car with the cover and left their cars for eternity. These cars have not even moved an inch for a really long time some for a few years.  We have also observed people park their cars here and not close to their residence which would be located quite far. The parking needs to be done at their residences and not out here where commercial establishments find it virtually impossible to find parking. Another nexus is of the owner/shopkeepers who pre book the spaces infront of their shops/establishment with a chain, watchman, stones, parked car which are public land ;like Fawwaz Perfume, Wecool Imports, Studio Plus store, Double Decker Restaurant for their personal parking even though it is public parking, though we would want to know how this can be avoided or acted upon. The police would have to act on this to curb such acts.We would really like a change to happen either in the form of paid parking or deliberately remove cars which have been parked for a long duration of time which will definitely remove all these long term parking and thereby reducing traffic woos. Another problem is the building getting constructed have all the debris & material put out eventually blocking a few more car parks, if they clear this - it would also help in parking a few cars. We had read in the newspaper that the above mentioned roads are going to be taken under Pay & Park scheme after the success of the St Marks Road Model - is it going to happen soon.

title: Awareness on air pollution
description:
Sir, 

We must live healthy life here in Bangalore.
Air pollution is big take on above point.

What can be done?
Solution:
As our BBMP commissioner rightly pointing out, if vehicles goes 10% every year what ever you build roads will never enough.

From this we can understand we must encourage people to use public transportation, why people are preferring to use personal vehicles instead of public transportation? Don't we have proper connectivity? Please check with the them , we can able to answer to all of them.

Things to follow to see Bangalore as clean City.
1. Create an imaginable understanding on usage of public transportation and to avoid air pollution , first in school , colleges, software office.

2. Advertise a short film on this.
3. The last mile connectivity can be done by walk to avoid future diabetes.
4. Please feel free to reach out to me or like minded students on pollution , so they can give all ideas for creating awareness.

We are uneducated literates, thats all the problem is.

title: Aadhar Kendras suggestion/complaint
description:
This morning, I visited Aadhar Kendra in my location but in vain. As seems like, process isn't proper. 
Complaint : Present process, getting the token on every Monday, and that too only 10 to 30 tokens will be allotted, for receiving the tokens people stand in queues early morning in cold, irrelevant of ages, children and senior citizens too. And later once the token is allotted, the next date will be given, in order to create or update Aadhaar, and again same thing happens, like early morning in terrible cold, standing in queues. Which I don't feel it as good.

Suggestion : let the appointment slots be booked online, let the applicant submit his details, fix the appointment date and time, on which he wants to update/create Aadhaar. Based on the submitted details, let the Kendras/booths be diviided like which Kendra will do the updates, and the other set of Kendras should take care of creating new Aadhars. 
And let the user, print his acknowledgement, and ask the user to be present on scheduled appointed date and time.

And let the appointments be scheduled in time slot basis. Like if I book an appointment on 1st March 2019 9:00 AM, at XYZ Aadhar Kendra, the same time slot shouldn't be given to other applicants in this Kendra. 

Thanks
location: Shampura, Kaval Bairasandra, Bengaluru, Karnataka 560032, India

title: Huge traffic jams due to AET Junction bottleneck
description:
From past 6 months, traffic has worsened on Sarjapura road near Doddakannelli stretch during peak office hours due to bottleneck at AET Junction. Unfortunately, there is no alternative roads towards Marathahalli  apart from just outer ring road and Doddakannelli-Kadubesnahalli Road. Hence, all the traffic on Sarjapura road is distributed on both the streches and causing huge pile up of traffic on this road. The road is unscientific as it is does not have uniform consistent width. To add to woes, there is no lane discipline and which makes narrow width stretches as bottle necks before the junction.

Most of the times these days, it takes about 45 mins to 1 hour to just cross the AET junction from Andhra Bank, Doddakannelli (~2 KMs of stretch). Due to this , there is a huge loss in fuel and precious time.

As a short term solution, I believe BBMP and Bangalore traffic police should think of alternatives to de congest the AET junction and should think of laying parallel roads to outer ring road as a long term solution. However, it is upto agencies to think of best solution for benefit of citizens and city.

I wanted to know if there is any action plan in place by BBMP, Government of Karnataka and Bangalore City Police to provide a near term and long term solution.
location: Aet Junction, Janatha Colony, Doddakannelli, Bengaluru, Karnataka 560035

Ever since the new linesman has come since past 1.5 months, the situation has become GRAVE !! Normally, the water supply was supposed to be there yesterday at 12 noon, but there was NO SUPPLY yesterday as well.

It's a general opinion that the major problem lies with the linesman. Mr. Sridhar the incharge engineer was contacted several times. Yesterday, I made more than 10 calls which he did not answer. 

We are totally out of water supply. In this layout which is BDA approved, we are all Law Abiding citizens and we pay our dues legally and regularly.
